        "discriminators": [
          "Air plus hammering. Two co-present cues: a broadband exhaust hiss (high spectral_flatness, LOW harmonicity) and a fast periodic impact chatter (high onset_periodicity at tens of hits per second). A jackhammer and an air ratchet are both this.",
          "Against TOOLPowr: this is THE split in TOOLS. An electric motor is HARMONIC — a pitched whine, high harmonicity, low spectral_flatness. A pneumatic tool is NOISY and PERCUSSIVE — high flatness, low harmonicity, high onset_periodicity. Same duration, opposite spectra.",
